data.name: Mitsubishi Chemical Group Corporation
data.description:
We lead with innovative solutions to achieve KAITEKI, the well-being of people and the planet.

Mitsubishi Chemical Group Corporation is a specialty materials provider with an unwavering commitment to lead with innovative solutions to achieve KAITEKI, the well-being of people and the planet. We bring deep expertise and material science leadership in core market segments such as mobility, health & life sciences, and electronics, enabling industry transformation, technology breakthroughs, and longer, more fruitful lives for us all. Together, around 70,000 employees worldwide provide advanced chemistry-based solutions to deliver the core elements of our slogan—Science. Value. Life.

* The Mitsubishi Chemical Group consists of Mitsubishi Chemical Group Corporation and its group companies.

data.name: jER™ Epoxy
data.description:
jER™ is an epoxy resin brand with the longest history in Japan. Based on decades of research and accumulated technology, we are offering a wide range of epoxy resin grades with characteristic properties, such as low chlorine, low viscosity, transparency, flexibility, photo-curability, high molecular weight type, and specialized molecular structure type, to meet diverse needs of our customers.

 

*jER™ is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group

data.name: METABLEN™
data.description:
METABLEN™ is the trade name of modifiers, which have been developed originally by Mitsubishi chemical, a world prominent manufacture of methyl methacrylate resins. Adding a small quantity of METABLEN™ to various resins improves and increases their impact strength and processability, and further improves the characteristics, the appearance and the productivity of their final products.

*METABLEN™ is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group.

data.name: Acrylic Bead Resins
data.description:
Acrylic Bead Resins are a line of solid, spherical methacrylate and acrylate resins produced by suspension polymerization. The free-flowing nature of these resins allows for easy dissolution in a variety of solvents and monomers. Our acrylic bead resins are non-hazardous allowing for convenient handling, transportation, and storage and can be used in a wide range of coatings, inks, and adhesives applications.  

At Mitsubishi Chemical Group, we can provide you with a broader portfolio of resins than we can currently showcase on Knowde, with varying of molecular weights, glass transitions temperatures, and functional groups. If you are interested in exploring the full range of possibilities or require expert guidance, reach out by sending us a message request.

*Acrylic Bead Resins is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group.

data.name: SHIKOH™
data.description: SHIKOH™ is a UV curable urethane acrylate oligomer. It is used for inks, coatings, and adhesives to add various functions such as toughness, elongation and elasticity. SHIKOH™ is suitable for Ultraviolet beam (UV) and Electron beam (EB) cure system as well as thermal cure. We have wide range of grades based on properties.Bio-based grade is also available.*SHIKOH™ is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group

data.name: DIACRON™
data.description:
DIACRON™ are saturated copolymerized polyester resins used for coatings, inks, and adhesive applications.

They have good adhesion to metals, polyester film, polycarbonate, and can be cross-linked with isocyanates, melamine, and epoxies.

*DIACRON™ is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group.

data.name: Forzeas
data.description: Forzeas™ is biodegradable, compostable and bio-based compound polymer designed and produced by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation (MCC). Our unique compound technology can be applied to many varieties of applications. Also, it represents our company purpose  “KAITEKI”  with eco-friendly properties. Forzeas™ can be flexibly formulated and can achieve customer’s demands, polymer performance and biodegradable/compostable/bio-based certification.

data.name: BioPBS™
data.description:
BioPBS™ partially (bio-based polybutylene succinate) is revolutionary in its two-fold bio properties.

Bio-based: Using advanced technology from Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, it is both bio-based and biodegradable plastic.

Composable: Derived from natural resources, such as sugarcane cassava and corn, BioPBS™ is compostable into biomass, carbon dioxide and water. Products made from BioPBS™ can be disposed of along with organic waste. BioPBS™ has no adverse effects on the environment and is naturally compostable, without requiring a specialized composting facility.

data.name: Ertalyte® PET
data.description:
Ertalyte® PET grades have the following features:


	Good for both wet and dry environments
	High strength and rigidity - ideal for close tolerance parts
	Excellent stain resistance
	Good wear resistance and excellent dimensional stability
	Better resistance to acids than nylon or acetal

data.name: jER™ YX7105
data.description: jER™ YX7105 is a liquid-type epoxy resin with toughness, flexibility, and high stretchability. data.name: jER™ Epoxy YX7110
data.description:
jER™ YX7110 is a tough and flexible liquid-type epoxy resin. It can be used as an impact modifier for brittle materials, as an additive to increase impact resistance, and for stress relaxation to avoid cracking and warpage. jER™ YX7110 is an adduct formed from the reaction of epichlorohydrin and an aliphatic and aromatic polyol.

 

Features


Adduct formed from the reaction of epichlorohydrin and an aliphatic and aromatic polyol
Crack and impact resistance
Excellent flexibility and elasticity
High viscosity
Low warpage
Maintains flexibility even after full-curing


Applications


Coatings
Adhesives
Composites
Potting and encapsulation materials
Base film/sheet for wearable devices


 

*jER™ is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group.

data.name: jER™ YX4000
data.description: jER™ YX4000 is a biphenol-type solid epoxy resin with significantly low melt viscosity, low water absorption and a good balance between adhesiveness and rigidity against stress. It can be used for electrical and electronic applications. jERTM YX4000 is an adduct formed from the reaction of epichlorohydrin and tetramethylbiphenol FeaturesAbrasion, heat and water resistanceElectrical insulationWear resistanceProduct HighlightsSignificantly low melt viscosity (melting point: 108°C)Low chroline contentLow water absorption ApplicationsElectrical and electronic applications (EMC, solder resist, PCB)Potting and encapsulation materialsPowder coatings for ship bottomsAdhesivesComposites *jER™ is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group.

data.name: jER™ YX8040
data.description: jER™ YX8040 is a hydrogenated bisphenol A-type solid epoxy resin, with high molecular weight. It can be used for optical materials such as LED encapsulants and adhesives for displays.FeaturesHigh purityTransparencyLED-curableUV-curable *jER™ is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group.

data.name: METABLEN™ S 2001
data.description:
METABLEN™ S 2001 is a silicone-acrylic rubber-type impact modifier with high impact strength in all temperatures and excellent weatherability. It can be used with ABS, PC, PLA, and other matrix resins in a variety of automotive, aerospace and electric and electronic applications.

Features


Can be used with recycled plastics
Good weather stability
Low temperature impact resistance


*METABLEN™ is provided by Mitsubishi Chemical Corporation, a member of the Mitsubishi Chemical Group.

data.name: Ertalon® 6 SA PA6
data.description: Ertalon® 6 SA is a high-performance polyamide (PA6) material that boasts a combination of excellent mechanical, electrical and chemical properties. Its exceptional mechanical strength, stiffness, toughness and damping properties make it a versatile choice for a wide range of mechanical construction and maintenance applications.Features:Superior mechanical strength and stiffnessExcellent toughness and damping propertiesResistance to creep and wearExcellent electrical insulationOutstanding chemical resistanceBenefits:Durable and long-lasting performance in demanding mechanical applicationsExcellent resistance to wear and tear, even in harsh environmentsHigh level of electrical insulation for safety and reliabilityResistant to a wide range of chemicals, making it suitable for a variety of applicationsApplications:Mechanical construction and maintenanceIndustrial equipment and machineryAutomotive and transportation componentsElectrical and electronic componentsGeneral engineering and manufacturing

data.name: Ertalon® 6 XAU+ PA6
data.description: Ertalon® 6 XAU+ Polyamide PA6 is a polyamide PA6 material that is heat-stabilized and boasts a dense and highly crystalline structure. This material offers superior heat aging performance in air, making it a reliable choice for bearings and other mechanical parts that are subject to wear and that operate at high temperatures for extended periods of time.Features:Heat-stabilizedHighly dense, crystalline structureSuperior heat aging performance in airBenefits:Reliable wear resistance and performance at service temperatures over 60°C (140°F)Ideal for use in bearings and other mechanical parts that are subject to wear and that operate at high temperatures for extended periods of timeApplications:Bearings and other mechanical parts in high temperature environmentsIndustrial machinery and equipmentAutomotive and transportation industriesOther applications where heat and wear resistance are critical factors.

data.name: Ertalon® 4.6 PA4.6
data.description: Ertalon® 4.6 and Nylatron® 4.6 are advanced polyamide PA46 shapes that are known for their superior heat aging resistance and ability to retain outstanding stiffness and creep resistance over a wide range of temperatures.Features:Superior heat aging resistanceRetains outstanding stiffness and creep resistance at high temperaturesOutperforms PA6, PA66, POM, and PET in extreme environmentsBenefits:Ideal for use in extreme environments where traditional materials fall shortCan withstand high temperatures without losing mechanical propertiesSuitable for a wide range of applications, including bushings, bearings, gears, pulleys, sheaves, wear pads, valve seats, seals, and conveyor wear componentsApplications:Bushings and bearings in extreme temperature environmentsGears and pulleys in high-heat industrial settingsWear pads and valve seats in harsh chemical environmentsSeals and conveyor wear components in high-temperature applications.

data.name: Ertalon® LFX PA6
data.description: Ertalon® LFX PA6 / Nylatron® LFX Polyamide PA6 internally lubricated shapes are specially formulated to withstand the demands of unlubricated, highly loaded, and slowly moving parts applications. This high-performance material offers a unique combination of mechanical properties, including high strength, stiffness, hardness, and toughness, as well as excellent sliding properties, high mechanical damping capabilities, and exceptional electrical insulation properties.Features:Internally lubricatedHigh mechanical strength, stiffness, hardness, and toughnessExcellent sliding propertiesHigh mechanical damping capabilitiesExceptional electrical insulating propertiesBenefits:Can withstand the demands of unlubricated, highly loaded, and slowly moving parts applicationsOffers a unique combination of mechanical propertiesProvides excellent performance in extreme conditionsMinimizes the need for external lubricationApplications:Pharmaceutical, biotechnology, medical, and processing marketsIdeal for use in unlubricated, highly loaded, and slowly moving parts applications such as gears, bearings, and bushingsCan be used in a wide range of industries where high performance, durability, and low maintenance are required.

data.name: Ertalon® 66 GF30 PA66
data.description: Ertalon® 66 GF30 / Nylatron® GF30 is a 30% glass fiber-reinforced and heat-stabilized polyamide PA66. This material offers superior strength, stiffness, creep resistance, and dimensional stability, while also maintaining excellent wear resistance properties.Features:Increased strength and stiffnessExcellent creep resistanceDimensional stabilityGood fatigue resistanceHigh mechanical damping abilityGood sliding propertiesExcellent wear resistanceGood electrical insulating propertiesGood resistance to high energy radiationGood machinabilityBenefits:Can withstand high loads and temperaturesIdeal for sleeve and slide bearings, wear pads, rollers, pulleys, scrapers, gear wheels, sprockets, star wheels and insulatorsCan be used in various industries such as pharmaceutical, biotechnology, medical and processing markets.Applications:Sleeve and slide bearingsWear padsRollersPulleysScrapersGear wheelsSprocketsStar wheelsInsulators.

data.name: Ertalon® 66 SA  PA66
data.description: Ertalon® 66 SA / Nylatron® 101 Polyamide PA66 unmodified shapes are characterized by their superior combination of strength and toughness. Compared to other unmodified nylon grades, Nylatron® 101 PA66 / Ertalon® 66 SA PA66 components possess superior mechanical strength, stiffness, wear resistance, in addition to displaying one of the highest melting points of all PA66 materials. Due to these properties, and this grade’s FDA and EU food compliant composition, Nylatron® 101 PA66 / Ertalon® 66 SA PA66 is often specified for screw machined electrical insulators, bushings, bearings, gears, roller wheels, star wheels, and seals.

data.name: Ertalon® 6PLA PA6
data.description: Ertalon® 6PLA / Nylatron® MC 907 is a high-performance, unmodified cast nylon 6 grade that offers exceptional strength, hardness, creep resistance, and heat aging properties. This grade is also FDA and EU food contact compliant, making it ideal for use in the food processing and packaging industry.Features:High mechanical strength, stiffness, and hardnessGood resistance to creep, wear, fatigue, and heat agingGood sliding properties and machinabilityElectrical insulation and resistance to gamma and x-ray radiationBenefits:Can withstand high loads and extreme temperaturesProvides reliable performance in harsh environmentsEasy to machine for custom applicationsSafe for use in food contact applicationsApplications:Gears, rollers, wheels, bearings, and conveyor wear parts in the food processing and packaging industryOther applications that require high strength and hardness, such as sleeve and slide bearings, wear pads, rollers, pulleys, scrapers, gear wheels, sprockets, star wheels, and insulators.

Together, around 70,000 employees worldwide provide advanced chemistry-based solutions to deliver the core elements of our slogan—Science. Value. Life.

* The Mitsubishi Chemical Group consists of Mitsubishi Chemical Group Corporation and its group companies.
